						<summary>

						<p>On a rock to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kōnēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ Year 13:</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged epigraph may be assigned to the 13th Century on grounds of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records an order of the king probably issued to the people of Dēviyartuṟai in Aṇḍa-nāḍu for the purpose of some constructions.</p>						

						<p>One Vikramachōḷa figures as a signatory of the above order.</p>						

						</summary>
